 sociologists, anthropologists, and religious studies scholars, some of whom are personally connected to polygamous families, seek to complicate a conversation that is more often simplified. Thoughtful and persuasive, Polygamy's Rights and Wrongs is both a close consideration of polygamy -- its historical place and its presence in contemporary society -- and a challenging reflection on the ways in which we value family and intimacy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aNon-monogamous relationships. 0aPolygamyxLaw and legislationzCanada. 0aPolygamyxSocial aspectszCanada. 0aPolygamyxSocial aspects. 0aPolygamyzCanada. 0aPolygamy. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / Marriage & Family.2bisacsh1 aBeaman, Lori G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeaman, Lori G., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBerger, Benjamin L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBradley-Evans, Martha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCalder, Gillian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCalder, Gillian, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCampbell, Angela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDenike, Margaret, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEisenberg, Avigail, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Arta Blanche, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Rebecca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorphy, Frances, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSelby, Jennifer A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook